An eight-part video series called, Baby Trade, Tracking the Truth, has been nominated for "Best Use of Social Media" at the upcoming International News Media Awards. The South African National Editors' Forum has expressed outrage that a story that was completely discredited has been shortlisted. The story was published by Independent Media, who still claim that the decuplets are real. The Gauteng government is pursuing legal action. SANEF's Sbu Ngalwa discussed this with eNCA's Dan Moyane. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - An eight-part video series called, Baby Trade, Tracking the Truth, has been nominated for "Best Use of Social Media" at the upcoming International News Media Awards. The South African National Editors' Forum has expressed outrage that a story that was completely discredited has been shortlisted. READ:Â Gauteng 'Decuplets' | Piet Rampedi facing legal action The story was published by Independent Media, who still claim that the decuplets are real. The Gauteng government is pursuing legal action. *SANEF's Sbu Ngalwa discussed this with eNCA's Dan Moyane in the interview above.